                      Last Places West Africa organizes  trips throughout the year, although the best time to travel to Ivory Coast is  from January to December, where you have a warm climate for very hot weather  and only moderate precipitation. The average maximum temperature in Ivory Coast  is 38 ° C in January and 31 ° C in July.</p>
                    <p><strong>Eating in Ivory Coast</strong><br>
                      Abidjan and other centers have  restaurants that serve French, Italian, Caribbean, Lebanese and Vietnamese  cuisine. There is a growing number of restaurants serving African cuisine aimed  at foreigners. The traditional dishes are kedjenou (chicken with different  vegetables and wrapped in banana leaves), nvoufou' bananas (pasta or yam mass  mixed with palm oil and seasoned with aubergines) and attieké (cassava dish).  The best area for spicy African food is the Treichville district of Abidjan. <br>
  <strong>Photography in Ivory Coast</strong><br>
                      Avoid photographing military or  police controls. Better not to photograph official buildings and ask permission  to take pictures of people or their houses.<br>
