  <strong>Best time to travel to Burkina Faso - Climate of  Burkina Faso</strong><br>
                      Last Places West Africa organizes  trips to Burkina Faso throughout the year.<br>
                      The months of January and February  are perfect for observing the fauna although the dusty Harmattan can produce  hail. It is convenient to avoid the hot season (April-May). The rainy season  falls between June and September and can make it difficult to visit some more  remote villages. From October to December is a fantastic time, with green  landscapes and pleasant temperatures.</p>
                    <p><strong>Eating in Burkina Faso</strong><br>
                      Burkina cuisine is based on basic  dishes such as wheat sorghum, corn, peanuts, potatoes, beans, yams, millet,  rice, okra (gombo), rice, millet and corn. Roasted meat is popular in Burkina  Faso and the most common meats are lamb, lamb, chicken, goat, meat and fish.  The vegetables Burkina people eat, in addition to yams, potatoes and okra, are  tomatoes, zucchini, carrots, leeks, onions, beets, pumpkins, cucumbers,  cabbage, sorrel and the spinach.</p>
