                      Last Places West Africa organizes  trips to Togo throughout the year. It is best to visit Togo during the colder  months (although it is always very hot): April to July and September to  November.</p>
                    <p><strong>Eating in Togo</strong><br>
                      Togo food is particularly good.  Most restaurants have a tendency towards French cuisine, although some serve  African dishes. Dishes include gravy meals, soups based on palm kernel, peanut  and corn. Meat, poultry and seafood are plentiful and well prepared, such as  vegetables and local fruit. A popular dish is rice with peanut sauce. </p>
