                    <p><strong>Chad</strong><br>
                      <strong>What does Chad offer?</strong><br>
                      Chad is a great destination,  recommended for any traveler interested in natural spaces that are still  unspoilt and not crowded by mass tourism. Chad is huge, with a purely Saharan  north and a semi-arid south, covered with wooded savannah. Chad has great potential  and it is known, more and more tour operators get into Chad, exploring new  deserts, new tribes and ceremonies. The lack of comfortable accommodation  restrains some travelers, but this will soon change if peaceful moment in the  country is consolidated in the coming years.  In Last Places West Africa we have made a firm  commitment to Chad for its beauty, authenticity and unlimited potential.</p>
                    <p><strong>Last Places West Africa recommends:</strong><br>
                      -Ennedi Desert, with beautiful rock  formations and impressive rock paintings.<br>
                      -Nomadic lifestyle throughout the  country.<br>
                      - Woodabe Gerewol from Chad.<br>
                      -Sara and Mboum tribal ceremonies  in the South.<br>
                      -Leré Royal Palace and granaries  (Moundang tribe).<br>
                      - Kotoko and Buduma tribes living  in Lake Chad&rsquo;s islands.<br>
                      -Tibesti Desert, remote and  fantastic (border with Libya).<br>
                      - Zakouma National Park, last  refuge of the Darfurian giraffe (subspecies), herds of elephants, western  lions, and since 2019 black rhinos (originating in South Africa).<br>
                      - Sultanates to be discovered from  Abeché to Massenya.<br>
                      -Festival of the Saharan Cultures in  Eastern Ennedi (usually around March).<br>
                      -Domed huts of the Musgum tribe in  the Logone River (Bongor area).</p>
