                      Yellow fever. Recommended  prophylaxis against malaria.</p>
                    <p><strong>Security in Chad</strong><br>
                      The instability of Libya and the socio-political  situation in the Central African Republic discourage visiting those border regions.  Lake Chad area is also restricted due to Boko Haram actions in recent times. The  rest of the country is calm but it is key to go with experienced guides and  fixers in the Sahara Desert to avoid getting lost and help managing military  controls.<br>
  <strong>Money in Chad</strong><br>
                      The national currency is the CFA  Franc, common currency in several countries (former French colonies) of West  and Central Africa. You can exchange Euros for the local currency at airports,  banks, or exchange houses. The Last Places West Africa guide can help you  exchange money. The places that allow paying by credit card are counted, so  money must be carried in cash.</p>
