  <strong>Best time to travel to Chad - Climate of Chad</strong><br>
                      Last Places West Africa organizes  trips to Chad throughout the year, although the best time is between November  and March (heat, but less and no rain in the South). Between March and April is  the ideal time to see wildlife in the Zakouma National Park. Between July and  September many tracks are complicated (center-south) by the rains. The Gerewol  is usually held in September, at the end of the rains.</p>
                    <p><strong>Eating in Chad</strong><br>
                      Chad's cuisine is a mixture of  Arabic and French cuisine, since it was invaded by them. Much river fish is  consumed, such as carp or perch, especially sun-dried and smoked. In the south  it is cooked more with rice, tubers, such as potatoes or cassava and vegetables  like okra, all very spicy. Fruits typical of warm countries, such as mango, are  consumed either whole or in milkshakes and a lot of carcadé is also consumed.  They have native millet beers. Chad smells corn, salted fish, chilli pepper,  onion, peanut butter, mango, cardamom and hibiscus.<br>
