                      Taking into account that in São  Tomé and Príncipe it rains quite a lot as a tropical country, there are some  periods where it does a little less. Between June and September, coinciding  with the European summer, there is a kind of dry season. Likewise, January,  February and part of March do not register the same amount of water as in the  other months. We must also say that there are not constant rains and momentary showers.  Equally it is convenient to be made to the idea that the cloudy days are much  easier than the sunny ones. That is to say, it is a destination of nature and  beaches, but not of sun in abundance. That must be clear before leaving. There  is a constant average of temperatures that go all the year around 27 degrees  (with enough humidity). Even so, any time of the year is good for traveling to  Sao Tome and Principe. In November (and until March) the turtles come to spawn  (and from February to almost May you can see the turtles coming out of the  nests), the best visibility for diving is between December and March, carnivals  are celebrated in full February. And before summer the flights are much cheaper  as well as the accommodations. Some people also say that November, although it  is rainy, gives an excellent light for photography. And those who seek to see  birds, in the first months of the year begins the change of plumage for males  to attract their potential partners. Last Places West Africa organizes trips to  Sao Tome and Principe throughout the year.</p>
