                      Yellow fever. Recommended  prophylaxis against malaria. Ebola shoots every so often. Find out before  traveling according to which zones.</p>
                    <p><strong>Security in the Democratic Republic of the Congo</strong><br>
                      The Democratic Republic of the  Congo is a huge country with enormous social problems. A long civil war, the  internal struggle for mining territories, and a weak state make it difficult to  travel around the country. The team of professional guides of Last Places West  Africa knows how to move around the country and has good contacts to facilitate  commuting and visits. The most conflictive regions are those bordering Uganda  and Rwanda, given the high presence of armed bands that compete for control of  the mining resources of the region. In 2018 there was a major Ebola outbreak  near the city of Mbandaka north of Kinshasa. In the capital, as well as in  other large cities of the country, the traveler must increase precautions and  avoid certain neighborhoods or streets at night. The key is to always go with a  guide that knows how to move and read each situation.</p>
                    <p><strong>Money in the Democratic Republic of the Congo</strong><br>
                      The local currency is the Congolese  Franc. The economy is, however, strongly dollarized.<br>
                      Although in some occasions the  payment in euros is accepted, the most used currency is the dollar, as long as  they are dollars issued from the year 1996 - big head in those of 100 dollars  -, not being generally admitted the one dollar bill. Weak bills are not  allowed, even if they are only slightly damaged. At the airport during the  baggage registers several extortion attempts for holding money have been  reported in the past.<br>
                      The DRC is a &quot;cash&quot;  country. However, credit cards (Visa and Master Card) are increasingly accepted  in some hotels (Grand Hotel, Memling, Fleuve), airlines, supermarkets and  restaurants. ATMs have recently started to appear, particularly in large  cities. </p>
                    <p><strong>Schedule in the Democratic Republic of the Congo</strong><br>
                      GMT / UTC + 1. </p>
                    <p><strong>Electricity and charging camera / mobile batteries in  the Democratic Republic of the Congo</strong><br>
                      Voltage: 220 V Plugs: Type C  Frequency: 50 Hz<strong></strong><br>
                      To charge the batteries during the  camping days, we will have the plugs of the vehicles themselves as well as a  generator that will facilitate.<br>
  <strong>Best time to travel to the Democratic Republic of the  Congo - Climate of the Democratic Republic of the Congo</strong><br>
                      Last Places West Africa organizes  trips to the Democratic Republic of the Congo throughout the year. Country  crossed by the Ecuador this implies that when it is dry in the north in the  south it rains and vice versa. The region of Kinshasa and all the center and  south, the dry season goes from April to October, while in the north it rains  during that period. The ideal time to visit the Democratic Republic of the  Congo is during the European summer.</p>
                    <p><strong>Eating in the Democratic Republic of the Congo</strong><br>
                      Outside of Kinshasa the gastronomic  offer is simple, marked by tubers and game meat.</p>
                    <p><strong>Photography in the Democratic Republic of the Congo</strong><br>
                      Avoid photographing military or  police controls. Better not to photograph official buildings and ask permission  to take pictures of people or their houses.</p>
